        public Predicate accept(Visitor visitor,
               Indexes indexes)
        Description copied from interface: VisitablePredicate
        Accept visitor. Predicate can either return it's own instance if no modification was done as a result of the visit. In the case there is a change needed then the predicate has to return changed copy of itself. Predicates has to be treated as immutable for optimization purposes.
